       <center>What are Programming Paradigm's?</center>
       <h1>A way to think of it is,</h1>
    <ol>
      <li>What are they?</li>
    <ul>
      <li>Most are Hybirds!</li>
    </ul>  
      <li><strong />The Four Primary Ones</li>
    <ul>
      <li>Functional</li>
      <li>Imperative</li>
      <li>Object Oriented</li>
      <li>Declaritive</li>
    <ol>
      <li>OOP Example<br>Sketchpad</li>
     </ol>
    </ul>
        <li>Turning Completeness</li>
      <li>Summary</li>
      <p> Program Paradigms are</p>
      
      <li>The concepts and abstrations used to represent the elements of a program (e.g. objects, functions, variables, constraints, etc.) and the steps that compose a computation (assignation, evaluation, continuations, data flows, etc.)</li>
      <li>Or a way to classify the style of programing.</li>
    </ol>
        
